  "title": "ISic003331. The Syracusans honour King Gelon, son of Hieron II",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"ὁ\">ὁ</span>  <span data-text=\"δᾶμος\">δᾶ̣μος</span>  <span data-text=\"τῶν\">τῶν</span>  <span data-text=\"Σ\">Σ̣</span>  <span data-text=\"υρακοσίων\">υρακοσίων</span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"βασιλέα Γέλωνα βασιλέος Ἱέρωνος\"><span data-text=\"βασιλέα\">βασιλέα</span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Γέλωνα\">Γέλωνα</span>  <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"βασιλέος Ἱέρωνος\"><span data-text=\"βασιλέος\">βασιλέος</span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Ἱέρωνος\">Ἱέρωνος</span></span></span>  <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Διὶ Ἑλλανίωι\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Διὶ\">Δ̣ι̣ὶ̣</span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"epithet\" data-text=\"Ἑλλανίωι\">Ἑλ̣λ̣α̣νί̣ω̣ι̣</span></span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"ὁ\">Ο</span><span data-text=\"δᾶμος\">Δ.ΜΟΣ</span><span data-text=\"τῶν\">ΤΩΝ</span><span data-text=\"Σ\">.</span><span data-text=\"υρακοσίων\">ΥΡΑΚΟΣΙΩΝ</span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"βασιλέα Γέλωνα βασιλέος Ἱέρωνος\"><span data-text=\"βασιλέα\">ΒΑΣΙΛΕΑ</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Γέλωνα\">ΓΕΛΩΝΑ</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"βασιλέος Ἱέρωνος\"><span data-text=\"βασιλέος\">ΒΑΣΙΛΕΟΣ</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Ἱέρωνος\">ΙΕΡΩΝΟΣ</span></span></span><br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Διὶ Ἑλλανίωι\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Διὶ\">...</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"epithet\" data-text=\"Ἑλλανίωι\">Ε...Ν...</span></span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic003331_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-28.\" src=\"ISic003331_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003331.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-28.\" src=\"ISic003331-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic003331_left_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-28.\" src=\"ISic003331_left_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003331_left.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-28.\" src=\"ISic003331_left-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic003331_right_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-28.\" src=\"ISic003331_right_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003331_right.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-28.\" src=\"ISic003331_right-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic003331_top_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-28.\" src=\"ISic003331_top_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003331_top.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-28.\" src=\"ISic003331_top-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic003331_rear_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-28.\" src=\"ISic003331_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003331_rear.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-06-28.\" src=\"ISic003331_rear-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text from autopsy (other editors do not bother to indicate those letters which are reduced to formally ambiguous traces, presumably on the grounds that the restoration is uncontroversial)</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>The people of the Syracusans (dedicate/honour) King Gelon, son of King Hieron to Zeus Hellanios</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The base attests to the title basileus for Gelon, son of Hieron, who was co-regent between 241/0 BCE and his death in 216 BCE. Palaeographically it is very similar to that in honour of Hieron II (<a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000823\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000823</a>). Zeus Hellanios is otherwise attested on bronze coinage of Hiketas, ruler of Syracuse for some of the period between Agathocles (d.289) and the rise of Hieron II at the end of the 270s (the coinage commonly dated to the period c.287-278 BCE), as e.g. <a href=\"http://numismatics.org/collection/1944.100.57056\" target=\"_blank\">SNG ANS 789</a>.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 56.1103.1.4 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a></li><li> Orsi 1895 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001713\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001713</a></li><li> Orsi 1896 400 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001709\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001709</a></li><li> Dittenberger 1915-1924 no.428 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000727\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000727</a></li><li> Libertini 1929 121 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001872\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001872</a></li><li> Dimartino 2006 705 no.1.4 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002022\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002022</a></li><li> Dimartino 2017 175-180 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10003126\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10003126</a>  </li><li> Prag 2017 122 fig.6 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001664\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001664</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Elegant wide and very regular letters with thinly carved strokes. Broken bar alpha; beta with equal sized loops; epsilon with short middle bar; kappa with short arms; mu with vertical first and last, middle strokes to half-height; omicron normally full size but small in line 2 (compression a factor); rho with almost fully rounded eye; sigma with approximately horizontal top and bottom strokes or very slightly open; omega full-size rounded and open with straight feet.</p> <p> Types list: <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Β-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Β type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Β-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Β type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Γ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Γ type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Δ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Δ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ι-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ι type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Λ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Λ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ο-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ο type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ο-type1.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ο type1.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-tyoe3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ tyoe3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Τ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Τ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Τ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Τ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type1.1</a> </p> Line 1  26-32  Line 2  27-33 (omicron 22)  Line 2  incomplete  Interlineation line 1 to 2  18-23  Interlineation line 2 to 3  20  </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
